Now I understand the issue. The `getDb()` in `packages/storage/src/db.ts` only checks `dbInstance !== null` but doesn't verify the Dexie connection is actually open. When `initDb()` is called, it closes the old instance (`dbInstance.close()`) before creating a new one — and if async operations captured the old reference, they fail. Additionally, `isDbOpen()` doesn't use Dexie's `isOpen()` method to detect a stale/closed connection.
